London Mayor Calls for Independent Oversight on Hacking Probe

-- B y   B l a n c h e   G a t t
-- 
2011-07-06T17:13:03Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-07-06/london-mayor-calls-for-independent-oversight-on-hacking-probe.html
Mayor of London  Boris Johnson  told
the U.K. Police Commissioner today that the investigation into
phone hacking allegations, including whether police officers
received payments from the News of the World newspaper, should
be subject to “independent oversight” and the Independent
Police Complaints Commission “should play a full role, the
Mayor’s press office said in an e-mailed statement.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Blanche Gatt in London at 
 bgatt@bloomberg.net   To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Colin Keatinge at 
 ckeatinge@bloomberg.net . 